Aston Villa 1-1 Southampton: Koeman says patience was needed
Media playback is not supported on this deviceSouthampton manager Ronald Koeman says his team needed to be more patientin their 1-1 draw with Aston Villa.His side fell behind when Gabriel Agbonlahor capitalised on an error from goalkeeper Fraser Forster, before Nathaniel Clyne equalised late on.Southampton's next three league games are against Manchester City, Arsenal and Manchester United.